<HEADLINE> Customs Officials Make Progress in Drug Seizures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- China's customs officials have
scored remarkable success in drug seizures in 1997, today's
International Business Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
They have seized 369 kilograms of all kinds of drugs during the
year, 1.3 times the 1996 figure, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Drugs containing ephedra vulgaris, drug-making chemicals and
mental medicines increased notably in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Officials of 10 Chinese customs offices were assisted by
drug-seizing dogs, used in 20 drug busts of 15 kilograms.  
</P>
